Libya Owns Prime Johannesburg, Cape Town Real Estate, Mail & Guardian Says

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-03-04T05:52:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/libya-s-government-owns-prime-south-african-property-mail-guardian-says.html
The Libyan government’s investment
arm co-owns some of  Africa ’s most expensive real estate,
including hotels in Johannesburg’s financial district and
property in  Cape Town ’s V&A Waterfront, the Mail & Guardian
reported.  The assets are owned by the Libya Arab African Investment
Co., which in turn is owned by the  Libyan Investment Authority ,
the Johannesburg-based newspaper said, citing an unidentified
person close to LAAICO, as the organization is known.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  